(1) The national symbols of the Republic are the— National
symbols
(a) National Flag;
(b) National Anthem;
(c) Coat of Arms;
(d) Public Seal; and
(e) National Motto.
(2) The form, words, description and use of the national symbols
shall be as prescribed.

There shall be a Cabinet consisting of the— Cabinet
(a) President;
(b) Vice-President;
(c) Ministers; and
(d) Attorney-General, as ex-officio member.

The following shall be prescribed: Legislation
on Bank of
